  "prompt": "Which library is better than the BGI library(graphics.h) for graphics in C++?",
  "response": "There are several modern graphics libraries that are better than BGI (Borland Graphics Interface) for C++:\n\n1. SDL (Simple DirectMedia Layer)\n   - Cross-platform\n   - Powerful 2D and 3D graphics support\n   - Good for game development\n   - Supports multiple programming languages\n   - High performance\n   - Example:\n   ```cpp\n   #include <SDL2/SDL.h>\n   \n   SDL_Window* window = SDL_CreateWindow(\"SDL Window\", \n       SDL_WINDOWPOS_CENTERED, SDL_WINDOWPOS_CENTERED, \n       800, 600, 0);\n   ```\n\n2. SFML (Simple and Fast Multimedia Library)\n   - Modern C++ library\n   - Easy to use\n   - Cross-platform\n   - Good for 2D graphics and games\n   - Example:\n   ```cpp\n   #include <SFML/Graphics.hpp>\n   \n   sf::RenderWindow window(sf::VideoMode(800, 600), \"SFML Window\");\n   ```\n\n3. OpenGL\n   - Powerful graphics API\n   - Hardware-accelerated\n   - Suitable for complex 2D and 3D graphics\n   - Steeper learning curve\n   - Example with GLFW:\n   ```cpp\n   #include <GLFW/glfw3.h>\n   \n   GLFWwindow* window = glfwCreateWindow(800, 600, \"OpenGL Window\", NULL, NULL);\n   ```\n\n4. Qt\n   - Comprehensive GUI framework\n   - Excellent graphics capabilities\n   - Cross-platform\n   - Example:\n   ```cpp\n   #include <QApplication>\n   #include <QPainter>\n   \n   QMainWindow window;\n   ```\n\n5. Raylib\n   - Simple and easy to use\n   - Good for beginners\n   - Cross-platform\n   - Example:\n   ```cpp\n   #include <raylib.h>\n   \n   InitWindow(800, 600, \"Raylib Window\");\n   ```\n\nRecommendation:\n- For simple 2D graphics: SFML or Raylib\n- For game development: SDL or SFML\n- For complex graphics: OpenGL\n- For comprehensive GUI: Qt\n\nChoose based on your specific project requirements and complexity.",
